  "title": "Introduction to the Piano: Understanding the Layout",
  "lessonText": "This lesson introduces the basic layout of the piano keyboard.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- The piano has 88 keys: 52 white and 36 black.\n- White keys represent natural notes (A, B, C, D, E, F, G).\n- Black keys represent sharps and flats.\n- The pattern of black keys is in groups of two and three.\n- Middle C is a key reference point on the keyboard."
  }
}
